OL,5,C'coaching'
OL,7,FMr Greaney told the court: "He has
OL,8,Frepeatedly discussed the content and
OL,9,Fnature of the evidence with Emma Croft
OL,10,Fand Lisa Green, during giving evidence
OL,11,Fand over the Christmas period.
OL,13,F"The assessment of the prosecution is
OL,14,Fthat the defendant has misconducted
OL,15,Fhimself, as has Lisa Green and Emma
OL,16,FCroft.
OL,18,F"What has occurred here is effectively
OL,19,Fa scheme to coach the defendant in the
OL,20,Fevidence he's giving.
OL,26,@oD@\OUuD@AOUzD@AOU
