OL,4,Cinvestigated for alleged evidence
OL,5,C'coaching'
OL,7,F"There's going to be an investigation
OL,8,Finto this by the police because, on
OL,9,Fthe face of it, there's been a
OL,10,Fconspiracy to pervert the course of
OL,11,Fjustice."
OL,13,FMr Greaney told the court the
OL,14,Fdevelopment created "complications and
OL,15,Fdistractions" and he did not intend to
OL,16,Fask Wellings about the matter before
OL,17,Fthe jury.
